[1] Case updates
- Sun 17 Feb 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health>
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_17fev19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 16 Feb 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 838, 773 confirmed and 65 probable. In total, there were 534 deaths (469 confirmed and 65 probable) and 294 people cured.
- 135 suspected cases under investigation;
- 1 new confirmed case in Katwa;
- 1 new death of a confirmed case at Butembo ETC;
- 3 new recoveries, including 1 release from the Katwa ETC and 2 from the Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 80 491 persons have been vaccinated [total numbers of people vaccinated in North Kivu, Ituri, Tshopo, and Haut-Uele can be seen at the source URL above].

