[2] Outbreak summary
Date: Fri 15 Feb 2019
Source: CIDRAP (Center for Infectious disease Research and Policy) [abridged, edited]
http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/02/ebola-still-claiming-lives-drc-cases-climb-835


Ebola still claiming lives as DRC cases climb to 835
----------------------------------------------------
The pace of new Ebola cases in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) slowed slightly last week, though the outbreak's intensity is still moderate, the World Health Organization (WHO) said yesterday [14 Feb 2019] in its weekly overview.

Meanwhile, in a daily update today [15 Feb 2019], the DRC's health ministry announced that the virus has likely infected 6 more people, in Katwa [North Kivu] and Komanda [Ituri], and killed 5 more, including an infant.

Community resistance still a factor
-----------------------------------
The WHO said Katwa and Butembo [North Kivu] are still the hot spots, though small widely dispersed clusters continue to be reported. One more health worker infection was reported, an individual in Katwa, raising that number to 68.

On 13 Feb 2019 the DRC's health ministry launched the 3rd phase of its response, which will cover the next 6 months, with the main goals of stopping transmission in North Kivu and Ituri provinces and prevent spread of Ebola to other DRC provinces and neighboring countries. To support the next phase, the WHO, the DRC, and their partners are asking for USD 148 million from the international community.

[Byline: Lisa Schnirring]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

